study specs/README.md, and @docs/plans/2026-01-19-unified-grammars-and-agents-design.md. Pick the task with the highest importance to implement next

# NOTES
- ALWAYS use jj over git for version control. You have a /jj skill that you can use to help with this.
- DO NOT proceed if there are any unresolved issues, warnings, or failing tests
- For rust code
  - Try using clippy --fix to resolve issues first before making hand edits.
  - DO NOT silence warnings without user permission
  - if the change required feels like it is unrelated to the current changeset, create a new task for it instead.
- commits should discuss what was done and why, not how.
- if you see an issue/compiler warning/etc, fix it first before proceeding
- if you notice an inconsistency in the docs, fix it first before proceeding
- make sure that all clippy warnings are resolved
- if there is a TODO that is blocking progress, address it first (eg. the rkyv serialization vs serde.)
- for any new serialization, use rkyv
- if a task requirement looks sufficiently complex, break it down into smaller subtasks, and stop the current run.
